Reduce the angular controller proportional gain (Kp) by at least 50%. The square-wave bang-bang oscillation at ±2.5 rad/s with a near-zero yaw reference is a textbook symptom of excessive gain driving the output to saturation limits on every cycle. Additionally, add output rate limiting and integral anti-windup clamping to prevent the controller from demanding instantaneous ±2.5 rad/s reversals. Suggested pseudocode:

  // Before:
  angular_cmd = Kp * yaw_error + Ki * integral + Kd * derivative;

  // After:
  Kp_angular *= 0.5;  // halve gain as starting point
  angular_cmd = Kp_angular * yaw_error + Ki * integral + Kd * derivative;
  angular_cmd = clamp(angular_cmd, -max_angular, +max_angular);
  if (abs(angular_cmd) >= max_angular) { integral -= error * dt; }  // anti-windup
  angular_cmd = rate_limit(angular_cmd, prev_cmd, max_rate * dt);
